videos.headline: Mayfield makes magic happen to set Big 12 mark
videos.description: Oklahoma's Baker Mayfield scrambles to the right before firing a pass across his body to Rodney Anderson, who runs it in for the 34-yard score. Mayfield now has a touchdown pass in 37 consecutive games, a Big 12 record.

videos.headline: Mayfield snubbed during pregame handshake
videos.description: Heisman front-runner Baker Mayfield attempts to shake hands before Saturday's Big 12 matchup, but is left hanging.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Mayfield snubbed during pregame handshake) 2017/11/18 ESHEET

videos.headline: Kansas summarizes struggles with high snap in Wildcat formation
videos.description: Kansas tries to get creative inside the five-yard-line with a direct snap, but the center launches the ball over Taylor Martin's head and Kansas would settle for a field goal.

videos.headline: Stanley's pass dropped, intercepted by Oklahoma
videos.description: Kansas' Carter Stanley throws it to his receiver running an under route, but it is dropped and Oklahoma catches the deflection for the interception deep in Kansas territory.

videos.headline: Smallwood powers in jet sweep for TD
videos.description: Oklahoma's Baker Mayfield sends Jordan Smallwood in motion and Smallwood takes the handoff 3 yards for the score as Oklahoma leads Kansas 14-3.

videos.headline: Mayfield completes pass, takes late hit
videos.description: Oklahoma's drive to score before half takes a big step forward after Baker Mayfield completes a long pass then takes a late hit adding 15 yards.

videos.headline: Brown takes screen across field for electric TD
videos.description: Oklahoma scores just before halftime as Baker Mayfield slings a screen pass to Marquis Brown who cuts all the way back across the field for a 24-yard score.

videos.headline: Oklahoma looks to open up offense despite poor conditions
videos.description: Oklahoma head coach Lincoln Riley says his team has had too many negative plays in the first half and that Kansas has done a solid job limiting their attack.

videos.headline: Sims keeps control for sideline catch
videos.description: Kansas' Steven Sims Jr. gets a foot in bounds and maintains control to make a 34-yard reception on a nice Carter Stanley pass.

videos.headline: Mayfield airs it out to Jones for big gain
videos.description: Oklahoma's Baker Mayfield sets his feet and delivers a long pass to Mykel Jones who concentrates to come down with the juggling catch at the 3-yard-line.

videos.headline: Mayfield adds to lead with third TD pass
videos.description: Baker Mayfield rolls right and completes a touchdown pass to Mark Andrews as Oklahoma extends their lead over Kansas to 28-3.

videos.headline: Sermon shakes loose for TD run
videos.description: Oklahoma's Trey Sermon hits the hole hard and explodes for a 25-yard touchdown as Oklahoma leads Kansas 38-3.

videos.headline: Mayfield's antics continue throughout game
videos.description: Baker Mayfield's antics toward Kansas players and fans may overshadow his three-touchdown performance.

videos.headline: Riley unaware of Mayfield's antics
videos.description:
Oklahoma head coach Lincoln Riley said that he did not see Baker Mayfield's various verbal 
 confrontations and gestures.

videos.headline: Mayfield, Oklahoma dominate Kansas
videos.description: After Baker Mayfield's pregame handshake at midfield gets denied, he throws for three touchdowns in Oklahoma's 41-3 victory.

videos.headline: Mayfield: 'I didn't lead us by example the right way'
videos.description: Oklahoma QB Baker Mayfield apologizes for his actions on the sidelines against Kansas.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Presser (Mayfield: 'I didn't lead us by example the right way') 11/18/2017 ESHEET

videos.headline: Mayfield goes off after handshake snub
videos.description: Kansas' captains decide not to shake Baker Mayfield's hand pregame, and Mayfield responds with several brash actions and three touchdown passes.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Mayfield goes off after handshake snub) 2017/11/18 ESHEET ENHL
